So Ross selflessly offered to take me.
罗斯就大方的提议要带我去

254
00:16:02,094 --> 00:16:04,255
What a nice story.
好感人喔

255
00:16:04,496 --> 00:16:06,088
So Ross was in college...
罗斯上大学时

256
00:16:06,298 --> 00:16:10,962
...and decided to jump at the chance
to take a young girl to her prom.
想趁虚而入 带一名少女参加高中舞会

257
00:16:12,738 --> 00:16:16,299
l definitely did not see
that one backfiring.
想不到会有这种反效果

258
00:16:16,809 --> 00:16:20,245
-l'm going to the bathroom.
-Take your time.
我去洗手间 你慢慢上

259
00:16:22,481 --> 00:16:26,713
l was a freshman and she was a senior.
So it wasn't as bad as...
其实我是大一，她是高三 所以没那么…

260
00:16:27,119 --> 00:16:29,917
Look. l know l've been giving you
a lot of jabs.
罗斯，我知道我一直找你麻烦

261
00:16:31,090 --> 00:16:34,321
lt's partly because
l'm very protective of Lizzie...
因为我很保护丽莎

262
00:16:34,960 --> 00:16:39,988
...and partly because
they just keep coming to me.
而且你的缺点实在很多

263
00:16:41,233 --> 00:16:45,135
l admit after all the
wonderful things Lizzie told me...
但是丽莎一直夸你

264
00:16:45,371 --> 00:16:50,570
...and the many, many, many stories
that Rachel has told me...
瑞秋又说了那么多事

265
00:16:51,477 --> 00:16:52,603
...well...
看来

266
00:16:54,113 --> 00:16:55,740
...you're not...
你也…没

267
00:16:56,615 --> 00:16:58,674
...all bad.
那么糟

268
00:17:00,252 --> 00:17:01,412
''Not all bad. ''
是没那么糟

269
00:17:02,421 --> 00:17:05,618
l'm sorry l was so harsh.
But you have to understand.
很抱歉之前对你那么凶 你必须知道

270
00:17:06,325 --> 00:17:09,761
l still look at Lizzie
like she's a 1 2-year-old girl.
丽莎在我眼中仍是个小女孩

271
00:17:10,295 --> 00:17:13,958
l know what you mean. l do that too.
我懂你的意思，我也有同感

272
00:17:15,501 --> 00:17:20,131
-l beg your pardon?
-l don't see her as a 1 2-year-old.
你说什么？ 不…我 不是把她当成小女孩

273
00:17:20,906 --> 00:17:24,865
l mean, l have a son who is 6
and l still think of him as a baby.
我是说我有个6岁的儿子 在我眼中仍是个小宝宝

274
00:17:25,110 --> 00:17:29,843
-A son?
-My ex-wife and l share custody of Ben.
你有儿子？ 对，我和前妻取得共同监护权

275
00:17:30,549 --> 00:17:33,313
lncidentally, Carol and l
are on excellent terms...
还有，卡萝和我的关系很好

276
00:17:33,552 --> 00:17:35,713
...as l'm sure you are with your wife.
相信你和你太太也是

277
00:17:36,021 --> 00:17:38,012
l'm sorry.
抱歉

278
00:17:38,524 --> 00:17:39,957
lt's unbelievable!
我真是猪

279
00:17:40,826 --> 00:17:43,488
Don't worry. l didn't realize
you were married.
没事，我只是不知道你结过婚

280
00:17:44,063 --> 00:17:47,396
We were. But that was just a....
我们是结过婚，那只是…

281
00:17:50,169 --> 00:17:53,627
That was just a big drunken mistake.
那只是酒后闹事

282
00:17:56,308 --> 00:17:57,502
You're back.
你回来了

283
00:17:59,845 --> 00:18:01,369
You two were married?
你们结过婚？

284
00:18:02,347 --> 00:18:05,839
l'm sorry.
You were talking about Emily.
抱歉，你在讲艾蜜莉

285
00:18:08,153 --> 00:18:11,350
We said we would meet
at the coffeehouse at 6:00.
钱德，我们是约6点楼下见

286
00:18:11,557 --> 00:18:12,581
We said 7:00.
我们是约7点

287
00:18:12,991 --> 00:18:14,322
We said 6:00!
我们是约6点

288
00:18:14,626 --> 00:18:16,389
The only way that l said 6:00...
我如果有讲到6点

289
00:18:16,628 --> 00:18:21,395
...would be if l said the sentence,
''Let's meet at 7:00, not at 6:00.''
应该是说： 我们约7点，不要约6点

290
00:18:22,167 --> 00:18:24,829
lf l had said 7:00, l would have said:
我如果有讲到7点，应该是说

291
00:18:25,070 --> 00:18:28,665
''My boyfriend is such a
wiseass. 7:00!''
“我男朋友真自作聪明” “什么7点”

292
00:18:29,842 --> 00:18:31,867
-Hi!
-Oh, my good God!
天哪。我的天啊

293
00:18:32,678 --> 00:18:34,737
-l know what time you said.
-What?
我知道你们约几点 什么？

294
00:18:35,214 --> 00:18:38,547
Well, l know what time
Chester and Marsha said.
我知道摩莎和钱特约几点

295
00:18:39,551 --> 00:18:41,519
What time?
几点？

296
00:18:41,720 --> 00:18:42,744
lnteresting turn of events.
真有趣的转变

297
00:18:42,988 --> 00:18:46,389
Suddenly it's my book to the rescue.
Let's see.
我的书突然成了救星

298
00:18:47,659 --> 00:18:48,990
Very interesting.
有意思

299
00:18:49,561 --> 00:18:52,155
Well this certainly clears things up.
这样就很清楚了

300
00:18:52,931 --> 00:18:53,989
What does it say?
到底是几点？

301
00:18:54,466 --> 00:18:58,493
l will tell you as soon as you thank
me for writing my book.
你们谢谢我写书，我就说

302
00:18:59,071 --> 00:19:02,507
